WEBVTT

00:56.306 --> 00:58.808
FINALE

00:58.892 --> 01:01.019
I don't know when it started.

01:02.604 --> 01:03.646
I guess it was...

01:04.481 --> 01:06.858
around the time Eun-u
starting locking eyes with me.

01:09.861 --> 01:11.821
I had to endure to survive.

01:15.408 --> 01:18.036
If I didn't suppress
my anger and emotions,

01:20.205 --> 01:22.165
who knows what I would've done?

01:25.210 --> 01:26.544
Did you ever think about

01:27.879 --> 01:29.380
leaving Eun-u?

01:33.218 --> 01:34.260
That's insane.

01:38.306 --> 01:39.516
I controlled myself.

01:41.601 --> 01:44.354
My life so far, my actions,

01:45.688 --> 01:46.648
my words,

01:48.399 --> 01:49.609
and even my thoughts.

01:51.820 --> 01:53.488
It's what got me through everything.

01:57.242 --> 01:59.327
Saying that I didn't think about that time

02:00.495 --> 02:02.622
or about Eun-u's mom would be a lie.

02:07.335 --> 02:08.753
I know it's hard to believe,

02:10.922 --> 02:12.590
but I feel nothing.

02:15.093 --> 02:16.719
Sometimes, it made me sad.

02:22.016 --> 02:23.309
On the day I was drunk,

02:25.562 --> 02:27.981
I found it hard to suppress my feelings.

02:31.609 --> 02:32.652
I'm glad you didn't.

02:36.447 --> 02:37.866
It's not just Eun-u.

02:38.950 --> 02:41.202
I'm sure you wanted
to console yourself too.

02:45.206 --> 02:46.249
Thanks.

02:47.375 --> 02:48.626
I'm the one who's grateful.

02:50.670 --> 02:51.880
You must've been upset,

02:52.755 --> 02:54.591
but you still understood how I felt.

02:58.428 --> 03:00.763
It's cooled off a bit. Let's drink.

03:09.355 --> 03:10.440
You should finish it.

03:22.535 --> 03:25.288
A verbal apology is one thing,
but that can't be all.

03:26.080 --> 03:27.081
Let's go.

03:31.961 --> 03:33.004
Are you refusing?

03:34.422 --> 03:35.924
That's not it.

03:38.176 --> 03:39.510
That wasn't my usual self.

03:40.511 --> 03:41.554
It was a mistake.

03:42.513 --> 03:46.517
Doesn't that just make me human?
It makes me seem more down-to-earth.

03:48.895 --> 03:50.521
Also, I should get at least one free pass.

03:50.605 --> 03:52.815
Isn't it a bit inhumane
to punish me when it's just...

03:54.901 --> 03:56.110
my first mistake?

03:57.946 --> 03:59.155
You're really talkative.

03:59.948 --> 04:02.116
Should I sign you up for the sober clinic?

04:25.014 --> 04:26.099
A week?

04:26.933 --> 04:28.351
Two weeks is too long.

04:28.851 --> 04:30.353
You'll only drink once a month.

04:30.853 --> 04:34.482
- Once a month? No way!
- Sober clinic it is, then.

04:35.066 --> 04:37.026
Okay, fine. I won't drink.

04:40.947 --> 04:42.156
You won't even take a sip.

04:42.657 --> 04:44.993
Violate it and I won't marry you.

05:48.931 --> 05:52.435
NO DRINKING ALLOWED. ENGAGEMENT WITH
JEONG-IN TO BE BROKEN OFF UPON VIOLATION.

05:52.518 --> 05:53.811
JUNE 26, 2019, YU JI-HO

06:00.860 --> 06:01.986
My father

06:02.862 --> 06:05.031
has been pondering about
the best spot for you.

06:06.991 --> 06:08.076
There's no need.

06:09.452 --> 06:11.287
I'm not that greedy, you see.

06:12.330 --> 06:17.126
All I want is a chance
to devote myself to the foundation.

06:17.835 --> 06:20.880
There's nothing more I want.

06:22.382 --> 06:24.759
I didn't know you were
that fond of my foundation.

06:27.553 --> 06:29.972
It's upsetting to hear you say that.

06:32.517 --> 06:35.728
So is your daughter
going to marry my son or what?

06:36.646 --> 06:37.814
What do you think?

06:37.897 --> 06:40.650
Do you agree with them marrying?

06:44.153 --> 06:47.073
That decision is for the two of them.

06:48.116 --> 06:51.536
We're only just the parents.

06:52.412 --> 06:54.080
What are parents supposed to do?

06:54.747 --> 06:57.417
We watch by with respect
as they make their choices

06:57.834 --> 06:59.252
and show them support.

07:00.711 --> 07:05.550
That's how I've treated my daughters
all this time.

07:13.307 --> 07:14.475
You're right.

07:16.310 --> 07:18.563
Marriage should be our decision.

07:19.564 --> 07:22.316
I think it was great for all of us

07:22.400 --> 07:24.318
to meet like this today.

07:26.946 --> 07:30.408
Jeong-in and I will get married
before this year ends.

07:36.080 --> 07:40.376
If you consider the weather,
fall would be the best time.

07:40.501 --> 07:42.044
What do you two think?

07:53.264 --> 07:54.599
My father's the issue.

07:54.682 --> 07:56.726
I've never been that worried about my mom.

07:59.353 --> 08:01.355
She may not show it on the outside,

08:01.898 --> 08:04.025
but I'm sure the decision
was tough for her too.

08:05.776 --> 08:07.487
It'll be even harder for your father.

08:10.072 --> 08:11.824
I don't want us to rush things.

08:13.493 --> 08:17.497
That's not the case.
This isn't just about me, you know.

08:19.248 --> 08:21.125
I hate making you seem like the bad guy.

08:25.254 --> 08:27.340
I'll be lying if I said I was unfazed.

08:27.757 --> 08:28.841
Still,

08:29.634 --> 08:31.928
it hasn't hurt my pride in any way.

08:34.055 --> 08:36.891
How can you be fine
when my family doesn't approve of you?

08:37.808 --> 08:38.893
Because of you.

08:39.810 --> 08:41.354
You approve of me.

08:45.483 --> 08:47.360
What? Do I not seem sincere?

08:50.238 --> 08:51.280
I think you are.

08:53.658 --> 08:54.659
Yes, you're right.

09:02.875 --> 09:03.876
What a great meal.

09:07.129 --> 09:09.757
Is your daughter
really going to marry my son?

09:11.842 --> 09:14.011
I thought we were done on this subject,

09:14.095 --> 09:15.721
so why are you bringing it up again?

09:15.805 --> 09:18.057
You know I don't even trust my own son,

09:18.140 --> 09:19.725
so how can I trust your kid?

09:21.435 --> 09:23.020
If that's how it'll be,

09:23.729 --> 09:27.316
let me also say that
I don't trust Gi-seok fully either.

09:27.400 --> 09:29.610
Then why did you keep
bringing up their marriage?

09:31.070 --> 09:33.489
It's Gi-seok who's rushing it.

09:33.573 --> 09:36.867
My Jeong-in didn't even bring it up once!

09:37.451 --> 09:39.203
I'm glad to know she has a conscience.

09:39.662 --> 09:42.498
Gi-seok probably has
skeletons in his closet too.

09:44.750 --> 09:47.044
Are you saying
that my son cheated on her too?

09:47.128 --> 09:48.588
Who knows?

09:49.338 --> 09:53.259
If I had known about this,
I would've taken photos too.

09:54.093 --> 09:56.304
Are you challenging me?

09:56.387 --> 09:58.848
- You think I'm scared?
- Sir!

09:58.931 --> 10:01.726
- Bring it on!
- Let go of me!

10:02.101 --> 10:04.186
- Seriously?
- Hey!

10:04.270 --> 10:05.396
- What...
- Sir.

10:05.479 --> 10:06.564
What's going on?

10:06.689 --> 10:07.898
- Let me go.
- Let me go too.

10:08.399 --> 10:10.484
I'm done serving you!

10:10.568 --> 10:12.570
What? Are you insane?

10:12.653 --> 10:13.696
- Sir, please.
- Sir!

10:13.779 --> 10:16.157
- I'm allowed to speak my thoughts!
- Sir.

10:16.657 --> 10:18.242
- You know my temper, right?
- Well, yes.

10:18.326 --> 10:20.828
- I can't leave like this.
- You think I've got no temper?

10:20.911 --> 10:22.830
- We should go.
- Let me take this off.

10:22.913 --> 10:23.998
- Jeez.
- Don't do this.

10:24.081 --> 10:26.500
- Bring it on.
- Sure, come at me.

10:26.626 --> 10:28.127
- Goodness.
- Father, please.

10:28.210 --> 10:30.338
- Bring it on then!
- Hey!

10:30.421 --> 10:32.590
- What the fuck is this?
- Consider yourself lucky.

10:32.673 --> 10:34.216
- As if!
- Let's go.

10:34.300 --> 10:36.385
- Consider yourself lucky too!
- You!

10:43.726 --> 10:45.686
Who does he think he is?

10:48.105 --> 10:50.149
Back in the day,
I would've punched his ass.

10:54.403 --> 10:57.657
He thinks that marrying off my daughter
is my only goal.

10:59.075 --> 11:01.160
What a joke.

11:07.583 --> 11:09.877
- What happened? Come this way.
- Okay, ma'am.

11:10.127 --> 11:10.961
Gosh.

11:11.045 --> 11:12.755
Unbelievable.

11:15.424 --> 11:18.177
- Watch your step.
- This way.

11:23.182 --> 11:26.102
My gosh! Why is he this wasted?

11:26.435 --> 11:28.187
You're unbelievable.

11:30.690 --> 11:31.857
Can you help me?

11:32.900 --> 11:33.943
Gosh.

11:35.945 --> 11:37.154
Goodness.

11:38.948 --> 11:40.408
- Thank you.
- It's fine.

11:40.533 --> 11:42.076
- No, wait!
- It's nothing.

11:49.125 --> 11:50.209
Thank you.

11:51.419 --> 11:52.753
I'm the one who's grateful.

11:57.258 --> 11:59.677
Did your father get home safely too?

11:59.760 --> 12:02.596
Yes, his driver just called.

12:03.013 --> 12:06.434
Right. Well, thank you for this.

12:07.810 --> 12:08.769
By the way,

12:09.687 --> 12:12.314
how did the three of you
gather for dinner?

12:12.982 --> 12:15.359
Did you have plans?

12:16.318 --> 12:17.319
Yes.

12:21.866 --> 12:25.703
It's about time we talked in detail
about our wedding.

12:31.751 --> 12:32.752
Mother,

12:35.212 --> 12:37.214
I must marry Jeong-in.

12:37.548 --> 12:38.549
Hold on.

12:40.009 --> 12:42.178
This is marriage we're talking about.

12:43.053 --> 12:45.473
What the two of you want comes first.

12:46.432 --> 12:47.850
I'm doing this for her.

12:49.059 --> 12:50.561
I don't get what you mean.

12:52.980 --> 12:54.982
She shouldn't be with Ji-ho.

12:57.818 --> 13:01.614
I know that he's in a different situation.

13:03.073 --> 13:06.660
Well, with regards to that,
I do feel bad for him.

13:07.077 --> 13:08.078
That's not it though.

13:10.122 --> 13:11.123
He's...

13:12.166 --> 13:13.542
not decent enough.

13:16.796 --> 13:19.173
I thought I knew him too,

13:20.299 --> 13:23.803
but you really shouldn't
judge a book by its cover.

13:26.055 --> 13:28.307
Do you know about the photos?

13:30.935 --> 13:33.646
You see, what happened is that

13:35.564 --> 13:39.318
since I couldn't give a straight answer
about our marriage,

13:39.443 --> 13:42.321
my father got worried.

13:42.404 --> 13:43.823
He did

13:44.740 --> 13:48.035
some research on his own
to look out for me.

13:48.494 --> 13:49.495
Ji-ho...

13:50.496 --> 13:53.791
just happened to be there
at the wrong time.

13:56.418 --> 13:59.088
My father is just as shocked, you know.

13:59.171 --> 14:01.340
He's worried about us not marrying--

14:01.423 --> 14:03.092
Yes, I get that.

14:05.344 --> 14:09.098
What do you mean Yu Ji-ho

14:09.181 --> 14:10.140
isn't a decent man?

14:12.434 --> 14:14.103
He came all the way to my workplace.

14:16.188 --> 14:19.191
He threatened me
with the photos that were taken.

14:20.317 --> 14:21.777
- He threatened you?
- Yes.

14:23.487 --> 14:27.032
He said that he wasn't scared
of anything in this world

14:28.200 --> 14:30.661
and that he'd make my father pay.

14:31.787 --> 14:33.539
What does he mean by that?

14:33.664 --> 14:36.083
Who knows what he'll do?

14:38.168 --> 14:39.753
He could be after money.

14:45.426 --> 14:46.510
Jeez.

14:50.055 --> 14:52.349
Don't worry though.

14:53.225 --> 14:56.395
I'll guide Jeong-in
back to her place soon.

14:57.605 --> 15:00.024
Ji-ho will be out of her life then.

15:10.784 --> 15:12.286
- Right.
- I'll take that.

15:19.585 --> 15:20.669
Hi, Jeong-in.

15:21.211 --> 15:23.839
My mom wants to meet you, Ji-ho.

15:26.467 --> 15:27.426
When?

15:28.594 --> 15:30.429
You're ready to spring out, aren't you?

15:32.222 --> 15:33.265
If I must.

15:35.225 --> 15:36.644
Why are you so at ease?

15:38.687 --> 15:40.522
It's not like I can avoid it.

15:41.815 --> 15:43.025
I like the attitude.

15:43.734 --> 15:46.362
Okay, I'll let you know when and where.

15:48.948 --> 15:50.324
Jeong-in, wait.

15:51.075 --> 15:52.034
Yes?

15:53.869 --> 15:55.663
I'd like to bring Eun-u, too.

15:57.373 --> 15:58.415
Would that be wrong?

16:00.584 --> 16:01.669
That's not it.

16:02.419 --> 16:04.630
I don't want to burden you.

16:05.464 --> 16:07.883
I have to introduce him sometime, don't I?

16:12.137 --> 16:13.764
I should've thought of that first.

16:14.515 --> 16:15.683
Sure, let's do that.

16:17.351 --> 16:18.477
I like it.

16:19.228 --> 16:20.229
Like what?

16:20.980 --> 16:22.648
That you think this is our decision.

16:25.734 --> 16:28.904
This is only the beginning,
so don't get too excited yet.

16:32.074 --> 16:33.575
No way.

16:33.993 --> 16:36.704
- That's amazing.
- It's really nothing.

16:36.829 --> 16:38.956
- Not you.
- Your boyfriend.

16:39.415 --> 16:40.374
Why not me?

16:40.749 --> 16:43.002
- His situation is nothing like yours.
- Exactly.

16:43.085 --> 16:46.422
He should be terrified, but he's so brave
to offer to introduce his son first.

16:46.505 --> 16:47.423
Exactly.

16:48.090 --> 16:50.300
Being a parent sure is different.

16:52.720 --> 16:55.264
They're the same age
but completely different.

16:55.848 --> 16:57.850
I agreed that it was a good idea too.

16:57.933 --> 16:58.767
It was too late.

17:00.227 --> 17:01.520
When I come over next time,

17:01.603 --> 17:03.355
I should buy something from the pharmacy.

17:03.439 --> 17:06.108
- Buy a couple of things.
- Got it.

17:06.191 --> 17:07.401
Don't forget your wallet.

17:10.195 --> 17:11.697
Seriously?

17:23.542 --> 17:24.793
Are you sure about this?

17:25.919 --> 17:28.464
Wouldn't it be awkward for everyone?

17:29.715 --> 17:30.966
What do you think?

17:32.426 --> 17:33.385
I agree.

17:34.553 --> 17:37.056
She wants to get to know you first.

17:37.181 --> 17:40.517
Wouldn't it be awkward with Eun-u there?

17:41.602 --> 17:43.896
Without Eun-u, she wouldn't
be seeing my true self.

17:45.147 --> 17:46.899
I get that, but...

17:47.941 --> 17:50.527
You may think that
because you are Eun-u's dad.

17:51.236 --> 17:53.197
Her family may like you right now,

17:53.447 --> 17:56.033
but that doesn't mean
they're ready to accept Eun-u as well.

17:56.617 --> 17:58.118
Jeong-in agreed with me.

17:58.869 --> 18:02.331
Also, I believe that
no matter how small the matter is,

18:02.664 --> 18:05.542
we should face it head-on together.

18:13.467 --> 18:15.469
Head back inside.
I'll call when I get home.

18:16.970 --> 18:19.681
I don't think
I was ever a father like you.

18:20.682 --> 18:21.934
What are you talking about?

18:22.684 --> 18:24.103
You gave me a lot and then some.

18:25.979 --> 18:28.524
I'm truly proud of you, Ji-ho.

18:29.149 --> 18:30.859
I'll get going then.

18:30.943 --> 18:33.070
- Drive home safely.
- Sure.

18:45.124 --> 18:46.125
Go on in.

19:08.647 --> 19:10.691
What are you still doing here?

19:10.774 --> 19:13.652
- Just go home.
- I need an answer.

19:15.362 --> 19:17.072
How can you marry a girl

19:17.156 --> 19:19.116
that's already with another man?

19:21.285 --> 19:24.371
Let's say you did. Can you still love her
for the rest of your life?

19:25.539 --> 19:27.374
Staying married is what matters, isn't it?

19:27.457 --> 19:29.168
- You idiot.
- Why...

19:30.836 --> 19:32.796
Why would you ruin this for me?

19:33.881 --> 19:37.134
There wouldn't be any issues
if you hadn't taken the photos!

19:37.467 --> 19:38.969
Are you blaming this on me?

19:39.094 --> 19:41.054
Is it my fault then?

19:42.931 --> 19:46.059
They're all upset that
you didn't approve at first,

19:46.143 --> 19:48.103
and today you picked a fight with her dad.

19:49.313 --> 19:52.316
Are you trying to help me
or ruin my chances?

19:52.941 --> 19:56.069
Does marriage seem that much to you?
Where's your dignity?

19:56.612 --> 19:58.614
This isn't the time
to worry about my pride.

19:59.072 --> 20:03.577
That prick is threatening us
with those photos you took.

20:03.994 --> 20:06.163
We must marry for your sake too.

20:06.246 --> 20:08.207
I have to force her down the aisle.

20:09.958 --> 20:13.253
Would you rather risk
the reputation you built so far

20:13.337 --> 20:14.296
for an issue like this?

20:15.923 --> 20:17.424
You have no idea what's going on.

20:20.219 --> 20:21.511
Unbelievable.

20:22.262 --> 20:23.388
It's so like him.

20:24.348 --> 20:26.892
Have you ever seen him
ruin something he put his mind to?

20:27.809 --> 20:30.520
He'll be the first of our friends
to get married.

20:31.813 --> 20:33.649
He's just meeting the family.

20:34.733 --> 20:36.860
You don't even have at least that.

20:37.277 --> 20:38.487
This again?

20:39.196 --> 20:40.530
And you do?

20:40.948 --> 20:44.701
We'll see who marries after Ji-ho.

20:45.577 --> 20:46.703
It'll be me.

20:50.332 --> 20:51.541
The door is opening.

20:52.459 --> 20:53.418
Good morning.

20:53.835 --> 20:55.045
Going up.

20:56.171 --> 20:57.422
What was that about Ji-ho?

20:59.049 --> 21:00.008
Oh, it's just...

21:01.677 --> 21:03.220
I think he's getting married soon.

21:06.098 --> 21:07.432
The door is closing.

21:11.728 --> 21:15.065
- Thank you. Bye.
- Take care.

21:19.736 --> 21:20.946
This is so like Si-hoon.

21:22.197 --> 21:24.950
Showering you with baby gifts
won't change anything.

21:26.326 --> 21:29.162
How did he become a dentist
with this level of stupidity?

21:31.790 --> 21:33.125
Don't unbox anything.

21:34.751 --> 21:37.045
You should've pressed charges that day.

21:38.547 --> 21:39.631
What do you mean?

21:42.217 --> 21:43.468
What are you talking about?

21:44.219 --> 21:45.637
Shouldn't it be just a lawsuit?

21:46.471 --> 21:47.806
I'll tell you about it later.

21:49.808 --> 21:51.393
Do it now. What don't I know?

21:53.979 --> 21:54.980
What is it?

21:57.399 --> 21:59.276
- I'll tell you later.
- Tell me.

22:03.030 --> 22:04.698
- Tell me now.
- Jeong-in.

22:04.990 --> 22:06.074
Get over here.

22:08.869 --> 22:11.455
Si-hoon assaulted Seo-in.

22:42.736 --> 22:45.197
PETITION FOR DIVORCE

22:59.961 --> 23:02.964
Okay, I signed it.

24:33.805 --> 24:38.185
Don't forget to be polite
when you meet the adults.

24:38.435 --> 24:40.228
Do as your dad says too.

24:40.687 --> 24:42.647
Make sure you don't make a fuss.

24:43.106 --> 24:45.066
Have a good time, all right?

24:45.525 --> 24:47.652
Enjoy yourself, my puppy.

24:48.820 --> 24:49.863
Bye.

24:53.783 --> 24:55.952
PYEONGCHANGSA LAUNDRY

24:56.036 --> 24:57.078
Bye.

25:16.223 --> 25:17.349
Ji-ho's here.

25:21.520 --> 25:22.521
Mom.

25:35.158 --> 25:36.159
Hi, Eun-u.

25:46.545 --> 25:47.629
Eun-u!

25:48.713 --> 25:50.257
Hi, it's been a while.

25:51.383 --> 25:52.425
There you go.

25:52.842 --> 25:54.928
It's nice to meet you. I'm Yu Ji-ho.

25:55.720 --> 25:57.347
Yes, it's nice to meet you too.

25:58.348 --> 25:59.641
We'll skip the greetings.

26:01.142 --> 26:02.477
We've met before too.

26:02.769 --> 26:04.145
Yes, it's been a while.

26:08.984 --> 26:11.111
Eun-u, this is my mom.

26:13.238 --> 26:15.240
- Go ahead and say hello.
- Hello.

26:16.825 --> 26:19.744
That was a sweet little bow.

26:22.914 --> 26:25.083
- Hello.
- Hello.

26:27.335 --> 26:29.462
- Hi.
- Hello.

26:30.380 --> 26:32.299
Don't you remember me? We met before.

26:33.633 --> 26:37.178
- You're the younger sister.
- What a smart little boy!

26:40.932 --> 26:42.267
Here. Have some water.

26:44.769 --> 26:46.021
Is the food yummy?

26:53.445 --> 26:55.572
Mom, you're burning a hole
in Ji-ho's face.

26:56.072 --> 26:57.115
Come on.

27:00.243 --> 27:01.494
You can be at ease with me.

27:01.703 --> 27:03.747
I'll answer any question you have.

27:06.124 --> 27:10.837
A single meal isn't enough
to get to know everything about you.

27:11.463 --> 27:14.507
We'll just take it one step

27:14.758 --> 27:16.551
at a time.

27:18.845 --> 27:20.805
I know quite a lot of things about him.

27:21.848 --> 27:22.932
I hope you'll be nice.

27:23.600 --> 27:25.143
That depends on Jeong-in.

27:25.727 --> 27:27.771
- How much is it worth?
- Do you want a piece of me?

27:33.526 --> 27:34.986
Eun-u, are you done?

27:35.528 --> 27:37.364
Want to go outside
and play with Aunt Jae-in?

27:37.447 --> 27:39.240
- Aunt?
- I'm not his sister.

27:39.991 --> 27:40.992
Would you like to go?

27:44.621 --> 27:45.914
Okay, let's go.

27:46.873 --> 27:48.083
Here are your shoes.

27:54.631 --> 27:57.967
She'll bombard you with questions now,
so I'll block what isn't necessary.

27:59.177 --> 28:02.722
You being this way
will only put him at a disadvantage.

28:02.972 --> 28:04.224
Why are you being this way?

28:04.307 --> 28:06.309
You're the one who wanted to meet him too.

28:08.311 --> 28:12.315
Actually, I wanted a few pointers
since you're more experienced.

28:14.025 --> 28:16.569
I don't know much
because my parents raised him.

28:17.487 --> 28:19.531
Still, I'll gladly share what I learned.

28:22.492 --> 28:23.868
I'm curious about one thing.

28:24.411 --> 28:26.663
What went through your mind
as you handled it all?

28:31.501 --> 28:34.421
I told you that
my parents mostly raised him,

28:35.004 --> 28:36.256
but he's still my son.

28:37.590 --> 28:39.676
He's living his life
with only me to look up to,

28:39.759 --> 28:40.760
so I couldn't crumble.

28:43.138 --> 28:44.389
The same goes for Jeong-in.

28:45.974 --> 28:47.892
She's putting her entire faith in me,

28:49.227 --> 28:50.854
so I'll protect her no matter what.

29:13.877 --> 29:15.712
The women in our family are crybabies.

29:39.736 --> 29:40.737
Welcome.

30:01.216 --> 30:02.300
Si-hoon?

30:07.639 --> 30:08.640
My gosh.

30:10.141 --> 30:11.267
What are you doing here?

30:14.270 --> 30:16.523
Why are you drinking
in the middle of the day?

30:18.858 --> 30:20.068
I'm getting a divorce.

30:21.528 --> 30:22.529
Sorry?

30:23.238 --> 30:25.740
Seventy percent of the reason is...

30:28.451 --> 30:29.744
Okay, fine. It's 50 percent.

30:31.704 --> 30:33.039
You're half to blame for it.

30:36.584 --> 30:37.585
Me?

30:38.378 --> 30:39.337
Yes, you.

30:40.338 --> 30:42.841
If only you had granted that loan

30:44.676 --> 30:46.511
or had married Jeong-in soon.

30:47.011 --> 30:49.722
I would've had enough time
to get back on my feet.

30:50.932 --> 30:54.352
All you said was that
you'd look into it and do better.

31:00.775 --> 31:02.068
What about you then?

31:09.033 --> 31:12.996
All you did was talk about helping me out.

31:13.955 --> 31:17.542
You kept saying you'd support me
and told me not to worry,

31:19.002 --> 31:21.713
but have you actually done anything?

31:23.006 --> 31:24.132
What have you done?

31:25.925 --> 31:27.760
You little prick... Want a drink?

31:30.638 --> 31:31.598
Eat more.

31:32.724 --> 31:34.475
Exchange some comments and wrap it up.

31:35.143 --> 31:36.895
If this drags on, it'll get awkward.

31:37.729 --> 31:38.855
My goodness.

31:41.482 --> 31:42.525
First of all,

31:44.360 --> 31:45.862
this must've been uncomfortable.

31:46.529 --> 31:50.700
Thank you for being so considerate of us
despite that.

31:51.951 --> 31:53.328
And most importantly,

31:55.371 --> 31:58.499
I should tell you that when I heard
you were bringing your son,

31:59.334 --> 32:01.085
I was quite flustered at first, but...

32:03.379 --> 32:05.924
I'm not sure how this will sound.

32:08.760 --> 32:09.928
I was touched...

32:11.429 --> 32:12.597
because I'm a parent too.

32:15.016 --> 32:15.975
I'm flattered.

32:17.018 --> 32:20.438
You could've said no,
so thank you for being so considerate.

32:21.105 --> 32:24.275
And this whole situation must've been
quite uncomfortable and awkward.

32:25.401 --> 32:27.320
Thank you for being so kind and accepting.

32:29.113 --> 32:30.031
Thank you.

32:30.865 --> 32:33.242
No, thank you. I really mean it.

32:34.619 --> 32:37.497
I think I'll bug Ji-ho a lot from now on.

32:38.164 --> 32:39.040
Sure, anytime.

32:40.375 --> 32:42.293
No, you'll have to get
my permission first.

32:43.419 --> 32:45.421
- My gosh.
- Goodness, you're so annoying.

32:45.505 --> 32:47.340
- You little...
- Gosh, hey.

32:49.968 --> 32:52.929
I told you.
He's a lot maturer than you are.

32:53.096 --> 32:54.472
Don't be silly.

32:54.639 --> 32:55.598
But...

33:03.356 --> 33:04.607
And you're probably aware,

33:06.109 --> 33:08.486
you have a long way to go
to persuade Jeong-in's dad.

33:09.654 --> 33:10.822
Yes, I'm prepared for it.

33:11.364 --> 33:12.824
I'll be totally fine,

33:13.366 --> 33:14.867
but it might stress Jeong-in out.

33:16.744 --> 33:17.745
No, it won't.

33:20.039 --> 33:21.040
Mom.

33:22.458 --> 33:23.501
Seo-in and Jae-in.

33:25.837 --> 33:27.005
I can do this.

33:28.297 --> 33:29.424
We'll get through it.

33:31.092 --> 33:33.636
We'll wait for Dad to change his mind
and accept Ji-ho.

33:34.804 --> 33:37.807
Mom, I'll always remember your advice.

33:40.393 --> 33:41.519
I know

33:42.395 --> 33:45.356
things that we never even expected
can happen,

33:46.524 --> 33:49.527
and there may be moments
when we'll regret our decision.

33:51.946 --> 33:54.532
But you know what? I'll still be okay

33:55.575 --> 33:57.910
because I'll have Ji-ho right by my side.

34:01.873 --> 34:04.500
I'll vent to him,
and he'll make me feel better.

34:05.626 --> 34:06.836
And before I even know it,

34:10.298 --> 34:11.466
I'll be happy again.

34:30.318 --> 34:32.653
So you're going to keep saying
it's not your fault at all?

34:33.446 --> 34:35.656
Why is it my fault that you got a divorce?

34:36.365 --> 34:38.826
How many times do I have to tell you?
You're pissing me off.

34:41.579 --> 34:44.040
You said you'd help me
so Jeong-in and I could get married.

34:44.665 --> 34:45.917
You said I could trust you.

34:47.418 --> 34:48.836
And what happened?

34:48.961 --> 34:50.338
Where's the guy who said it?

34:54.342 --> 34:55.384
Jeez, what the hell.

34:56.344 --> 34:57.929
Look at you talking all casually to me.

34:58.012 --> 35:01.140
- All right, fine.
- You expect me to talk politely?

35:07.105 --> 35:09.273
Do you even know how I feel now?

35:18.533 --> 35:22.745
Seriously, I never thought
a loser like Yu Ji-ho would...

35:23.996 --> 35:25.456
Who? Yu... What?

35:27.834 --> 35:29.961
How dare she even compare me to Ji-ho?

35:34.132 --> 35:36.092
What happened? Did you have a competitor?

35:36.676 --> 35:37.844
Competitor, my ass.

35:38.886 --> 35:40.096
There was no competition.

35:40.805 --> 35:42.223
That prick

35:43.307 --> 35:45.518
doesn't even measure up to begin with.

35:47.645 --> 35:50.648
I must say, this is quite shocking.
I'm shocked.

35:50.773 --> 35:51.983
He just doesn't compare.

35:54.569 --> 35:58.156
Jeong-in, my sister-in-law,
is seeing someone else?

35:58.823 --> 36:02.118
Why are you telling me this just now?

36:02.201 --> 36:04.287
You should've told me sooner.

36:04.370 --> 36:05.580
What could you have done?

36:06.247 --> 36:08.708
- Would you have--
- What? What kind of question is that?

36:08.791 --> 36:11.586
I would've told the entire family.
Then what would've happened?

36:11.669 --> 36:16.090
My wife's focus would've shifted
to Jeong-in,

36:16.174 --> 36:18.926
which would've helped me buy some time.
To do what?

36:19.010 --> 36:21.012
To patch things up. What a great plan.

36:23.431 --> 36:25.391
But whenever I come up
with an important plan,

36:25.474 --> 36:28.603
you always... You're just never helpful.

36:30.146 --> 36:32.190
Hey, I have an idea.

36:32.273 --> 36:34.317
Let's do this. Listen up, okay?

36:35.651 --> 36:37.320
A win-win strategy.

36:39.030 --> 36:42.325
I'll tell Seo-in's parents
that we're getting a divorce.

36:42.867 --> 36:43.868
Then what will happen?

36:44.118 --> 36:47.496
They won't want you and Jeong-in
to call off your plan to get married,

36:48.080 --> 36:50.625
so they'll keep pressuring you guys
to get married soon.

36:50.791 --> 36:52.460
Then it'll buy me some time,

36:52.627 --> 36:54.337
which I can use to mend my marriage.

36:55.838 --> 36:58.716
As they say,
God helps those who help themselves.

36:59.133 --> 37:00.635
"Happiness begins at home." Yes.

37:01.010 --> 37:02.929
Hey, it's an amazing plan.

37:06.015 --> 37:07.558
What do you think? Tell me.

37:11.729 --> 37:12.939
I must say,

37:13.940 --> 37:17.360
- the more I hear you talk...
- Isn't it a fantastic plan?

37:43.594 --> 37:44.720
Going to the washroom?

37:45.763 --> 37:47.515
No, I'm not.

37:54.397 --> 37:56.732
Let's just figure things out separately,
Si-hoon.

37:58.567 --> 38:00.278
Jeez, what do you mean by...

38:00.361 --> 38:01.988
Hey, hear me out.

38:02.238 --> 38:04.031
The washroom is that way.

38:04.156 --> 38:05.408
Hey!

38:12.623 --> 38:13.749
You're done.

38:21.424 --> 38:24.260
I HOPE YOU ONLY SEE, LISTEN, SAY,
AND DREAM BEAUTIFUL THINGS

38:38.024 --> 38:42.611
I promise you
that I'll protect you forever.

39:39.794 --> 39:40.961
What are you thinking?

39:46.675 --> 39:48.135
The reason I came back to Korea.

39:51.222 --> 39:52.765
You said you didn't want to study.

39:57.353 --> 39:58.729
I thought that was the reason,

40:01.023 --> 40:02.525
but I actually learned a lesson.

40:04.151 --> 40:05.152
A lesson about what?

40:31.512 --> 40:32.513
What?

40:42.440 --> 40:44.024
You didn't make any mistakes today.

40:46.110 --> 40:47.194
No, I just

40:48.404 --> 40:50.114
can't believe this day actually came.

40:52.575 --> 40:55.578
I'm also quite fascinated
by how my life is unfolding.

40:56.203 --> 40:57.163
Dad.

40:58.873 --> 40:59.832
Yes?

41:01.167 --> 41:04.587
Are you and Ms. Lee getting married?

41:06.755 --> 41:09.383
Yes. Why do you ask?
Does it make you feel weird?

41:10.885 --> 41:11.969
Then,

41:12.928 --> 41:15.890
is she going to be my mom?

41:18.517 --> 41:19.518
Yes.

41:22.354 --> 41:25.900
Yes, I'll be your mom.

41:33.449 --> 41:34.575
I'll be good to you.

41:36.994 --> 41:40.956
No, don't say that. The three of us
will get through this together.

42:01.268 --> 42:04.271
You used to nag me to date someone.
Why tell me not to get married?

42:06.065 --> 42:09.151
I need to live too.
You'd better not get married.

42:09.568 --> 42:11.570
I won't go to your wedding
or give you money gift.

42:12.863 --> 42:14.490
Are you worried that he might quit?

42:15.199 --> 42:16.450
I won't quit.

42:18.702 --> 42:20.287
Which area will you move to though?

42:20.621 --> 42:22.665
You'll have to think about
Eun-u's school too.

42:22.873 --> 42:24.124
Not for a few years.

42:24.208 --> 42:27.127
And I'll keep working here
regardless of where I live.

42:28.671 --> 42:29.755
Sign the pledge, then.

42:30.506 --> 42:32.341
Don't even go there.

42:33.676 --> 42:36.387
He's really sticking to his promise
and not drinking at all.

42:36.554 --> 42:37.638
He's so obedient.

42:38.264 --> 42:40.808
Can't you tell?
He'll be such a sucker for his wife.

42:41.392 --> 42:42.351
Who?

42:42.434 --> 42:43.561
- You.
- You.

42:45.437 --> 42:46.480
Jeez.

42:48.774 --> 42:49.942
Sign the pledge.

42:50.025 --> 42:51.443
- I told you I won't--
- Sign it.

42:58.450 --> 43:00.494
- About the other day...
- Oh, right.

43:01.245 --> 43:06.000
I drank way too much that day.
I'm sorry about what happened.

43:06.625 --> 43:07.710
It was my fault too.

43:10.588 --> 43:12.881
What's done is done. Just let it go.

43:14.466 --> 43:15.634
I wanted to talk about...

43:17.636 --> 43:18.762
What do you say

43:19.680 --> 43:21.307
to being a director after retirement?

43:22.683 --> 43:24.727
I can't really give you my position,
you know.

43:26.604 --> 43:27.688
That'd be crazy.

43:28.897 --> 43:30.232
What do you think?

43:31.692 --> 43:33.027
I'm underqualified.

43:33.694 --> 43:34.945
I think I'm underqualified,

43:37.615 --> 43:38.866
but it's... I mean...

43:38.991 --> 43:41.327
Come on. Stop beating around the bush.

43:41.785 --> 43:42.953
You don't want it?

43:43.662 --> 43:45.914
Gosh, it's not that.
That's not what I meant.

43:49.418 --> 43:52.171
You see, I'm just not sure
how I feel about it.

43:52.296 --> 43:55.341
Mr. Lee, are you still sulking?

43:56.550 --> 43:58.052
I said we should just let it go.

43:59.762 --> 44:02.181
Not everyone gets an offer like this.

44:03.641 --> 44:06.310
You're well aware of
how selective and fussy I am.

44:06.935 --> 44:08.020
I sure am.

44:10.064 --> 44:13.317
Well...
First of all, I appreciate the offer.

44:16.028 --> 44:19.657
But I'd like some time to think about it.

44:19.782 --> 44:21.408
What's there to think about?

44:22.910 --> 44:26.205
You can lose
by trying to be too calculating.

44:26.789 --> 44:29.416
Just give in and go along with it
if you want to be the winner.

44:29.500 --> 44:30.793
Trust me.

44:34.588 --> 44:36.048
Why do you keep chuckling?

44:41.929 --> 44:43.097
You can talk now.

44:44.598 --> 44:45.683
Well...

44:46.850 --> 44:47.851
Is there no chance

44:48.519 --> 44:51.105
for you and Gi-seok anymore?

44:57.194 --> 44:58.195
Dad.

44:59.655 --> 45:02.700
I think being a daughter who doesn't fill
her parents with heartache

45:04.118 --> 45:06.537
whenever they see her is more worthwhile

45:06.620 --> 45:08.288
than living a fabulous
and comfortable life.

45:11.792 --> 45:13.711
I know that you say harsh things to Seo-in

45:14.336 --> 45:16.255
because your heart aches when you see her.

45:20.050 --> 45:21.844
I know that you're not happy

45:22.469 --> 45:25.097
with my decision at the moment
because you're worried.

45:27.933 --> 45:29.560
Just be patient with me, Dad.

45:32.020 --> 45:33.105
I promise you this.

45:34.940 --> 45:36.900
You'll soon see me live a happy life.

45:39.528 --> 45:40.571
Please believe in me.

46:16.857 --> 46:22.029
PRINCIPAL LEE TAE-HAK

46:31.246 --> 46:32.247
Gi-seok.

46:34.166 --> 46:35.667
You've done more than enough.

46:56.688 --> 46:57.981
GI-SEOK

46:59.483 --> 47:00.692
I'm sorry about everything.

47:40.148 --> 47:42.025
Dude, you're being ridiculous.

47:42.109 --> 47:44.152
We should root for Korea.
Are you a traitor or what?

47:44.444 --> 47:45.946
Of course, I'm rooting for Korea.

47:46.154 --> 47:49.533
But the ball is round, you know.
With soccer, you never know how it'll end.

47:50.367 --> 47:51.368
Then let's bet.

47:51.743 --> 47:54.121
Okay, deal.
Which team are you going to bet on?

47:54.204 --> 47:56.832
Cut it out. You guys have to go home
right after the game.

47:57.499 --> 47:58.917
No, we have to drink all this.

47:59.376 --> 48:00.377
Just go home.

48:00.836 --> 48:02.379
Did you really quit drinking?

48:02.713 --> 48:05.090
Not voluntarily.
She forced him to quit drinking.

48:05.507 --> 48:09.177
- She has him wrapped around her finger.
- What are you talking about?

48:11.096 --> 48:13.056
- Here we go. Let's do this.
- Okay, go.

48:13.223 --> 48:15.517
- No one's blocking you. Go!
- Okay. Gosh.

48:16.101 --> 48:17.561
- What?
- Shoot! Pass the ball!

48:17.644 --> 48:20.022
- Shoot! Do it!
- Shoot! Come on!

48:24.943 --> 48:26.069
That hurt. Don't hit me.

48:26.528 --> 48:28.155
The ball hit the post.

48:28.530 --> 48:29.865
- Gosh.
- Jeez.

48:29.948 --> 48:31.366
That was so close.

48:34.536 --> 48:35.746
Bring me one too.

48:36.455 --> 48:38.540
- You're really not going to drink?
- No, I have this.

48:41.460 --> 48:42.836
Fine, you have to get married.

48:44.171 --> 48:47.424
Guys, you have to go home
as soon as the game ends.

48:47.507 --> 48:49.718
Okay, we heard you.
What's with all this nagging today?

48:49.801 --> 48:51.094
Stop nagging us!

48:51.887 --> 48:55.432
Yes, I'm going to bed now.
Are your friends gone?

48:56.016 --> 48:58.685
Yes, they left a while ago.
As soon as the game ended.

48:59.978 --> 49:01.480
You sound so down.

49:02.731 --> 49:04.274
Is it because you couldn't drink?

49:05.025 --> 49:08.028
No, I probably sound like that
because I'm lying in bed.

49:10.322 --> 49:11.698
All right, then. Go to sleep.

49:12.741 --> 49:15.077
Okay, you too. Sleep tight.

49:15.452 --> 49:16.411
I will.

49:17.829 --> 49:19.539
- Jeong-in.
- Yes?

49:21.291 --> 49:22.417
I love you.

49:29.675 --> 49:32.552
Good, done. We're good now. Okay.

49:33.887 --> 49:35.847
Goodness, are you a teenager or what?

49:36.348 --> 49:38.558
- "I love you"? What the hell.
- No, that was perfect.

49:38.642 --> 49:42.479
He needed to end the call like that
to make sure we can fool her.

49:43.146 --> 49:45.148
- I say it all the time.
- Sure.

49:46.108 --> 49:47.067
Jeez.

49:48.110 --> 49:50.570
Anyway, she's gone to bed.

49:51.405 --> 49:54.408
- Hey, what do you guys want to eat?
- I really don't think this is right.

49:54.491 --> 49:56.618
I'll just tell her you are here
and that we're drinking.

49:56.702 --> 49:57.786
Why? Don't.

49:57.869 --> 49:59.997
- Why ruin everything?
- I don't want to lie to her.

50:00.080 --> 50:02.332
- No, forget it. Get lost!
- Wait, just a second.

50:02.416 --> 50:05.210
- Get lost! We won't get caught.
- Gosh, wait.

50:05.711 --> 50:07.170
Hey, don't let him out.

50:07.254 --> 50:09.047
- Hey, hurry up.
- Okay.

50:09.131 --> 50:11.008
- Order something quickly.
- She'll kill me.

50:11.091 --> 50:12.759
- No, you won't die.
- She'll scold me.

50:12.843 --> 50:14.803
- Fried chicken?
- Yes, order chicken.

50:14.886 --> 50:16.805
- From that place.
- Where?

50:16.888 --> 50:18.682
- Oh, right.
- The place that delivers quickly.

50:18.974 --> 50:21.143
- Hey!
- Get some rest in there.

51:17.657 --> 51:19.576
Is Ji-ho having
a housewarming party today?

51:31.296 --> 51:32.672
Dude, you can't dance.

51:32.756 --> 51:35.509
I mean, all you can do is wriggle.

51:35.592 --> 51:38.011
Show us. You always do
that Michael Jackson dance.

51:38.512 --> 51:40.931
- Michael Jackson? I shall show you.
- Yes, dude.

51:41.348 --> 51:42.390
The moonwalk.

51:43.809 --> 51:44.810
See?

51:46.895 --> 51:48.396
- Jeez.
- You're pretty good.

51:48.939 --> 51:49.898
- Right?
- Yes.

51:49.981 --> 51:52.484
- I mean, look at this.
- What is that?

51:52.567 --> 51:55.570
I saw Michael Jackson at an event
in Chungcheong Province.

51:55.654 --> 51:56.822
- Show us, then.
- That's wrong.

51:56.905 --> 51:58.990
You're doing it wrong. Look, okay?
He enters the stage.

51:59.074 --> 52:00.575
Then he does this and...

52:01.868 --> 52:05.872
Then he does the moonwalk. Like this.

52:06.373 --> 52:07.707
You jerks.

52:08.875 --> 52:10.460
You crazy fool.

52:11.545 --> 52:13.922
- Let's just not dance.
- This guy is...

52:14.005 --> 52:16.925
- Promise. Let's never dance.
- Never shake your hips again.

52:17.008 --> 52:18.677
I'll kill you if I ever see you at a club.

53:31.041 --> 53:31.958
What was that?

53:35.503 --> 53:36.546
Hey, wake up.

53:38.340 --> 53:39.299
- Wake up.
- Gosh, why?

53:40.217 --> 53:42.093
- Just sleep here tonight.
- Wake up.

53:42.469 --> 53:44.304
- Hey, wake up.
- Why? Just sleep here.

53:48.600 --> 53:50.018
- Oh, gosh...
- Jeez!

53:52.604 --> 53:53.688
Hey.

53:54.231 --> 53:56.483
Hey, get up. We didn't drink...

53:56.566 --> 53:58.151
- Why...
- We didn't drink that much.

53:58.735 --> 54:01.238
Jeong-in, what are you doing here so late?

54:08.161 --> 54:09.371
You should've called me.

54:15.502 --> 54:16.628
Wait.

54:18.421 --> 54:19.464
I'm sorry.

54:24.386 --> 54:26.179
Yeong-jae, are you not going to study?

54:26.763 --> 54:29.933
I'm really going to break up with you
if you don't pass the exam again.

54:36.940 --> 54:40.235
Why do you keep saying no?
You obviously don't want to marry me.

54:41.361 --> 54:43.905
- Why are you being like this?
- It's written right there.

54:47.617 --> 54:50.495
I kept saying I can't drink,
but they persistently--

54:50.578 --> 54:51.913
You're such a coward.

54:53.665 --> 54:55.792
If you don't want to marry me,
just say so.

54:55.875 --> 54:57.377
Why pull something like this?

54:59.087 --> 55:01.256
- You're being too harsh.
- In what way?

55:03.341 --> 55:04.342
What?

55:04.634 --> 55:07.345
How am I being too harsh? Tell me.

55:10.598 --> 55:11.516
My stomach is upset.

55:15.562 --> 55:17.731
Where did you learn that? From Eun-u?

55:20.859 --> 55:23.320
I said I'm sorry. I'll never drink again.

55:27.115 --> 55:29.034
Do you think I'm angry because you drank?

55:31.453 --> 55:33.246
You've become a total fool overnight.

55:34.456 --> 55:36.750
It's impossible not to drink
when they're drinking.

55:37.792 --> 55:40.253
You should've just been honest.
But you said they left.

55:40.462 --> 55:41.880
You said you were in bed.

55:42.505 --> 55:44.299
You even said you love me when hanging up.

55:44.674 --> 55:47.052
- I really meant that.
- But everything else was a lie.

55:48.386 --> 55:49.596
Why did you lie to me?

55:51.097 --> 55:52.390
I didn't want to be scolded.

55:53.725 --> 55:55.393
Shouldn't you have feared this more?

55:55.560 --> 55:57.395
Did you really think you could fool me?

56:00.607 --> 56:01.733
Yes.

56:05.528 --> 56:06.863
Forgive me just this one time.

56:10.867 --> 56:12.118
All right.

56:18.416 --> 56:20.668
- I won't marry you though.
- Wait.

56:21.795 --> 56:22.921
You can't come in.

56:30.053 --> 56:31.596
- Here.
- Give it to me.

56:49.906 --> 56:50.865
What?

56:51.991 --> 56:53.034
That tickles!

57:00.792 --> 57:01.835
Here you go.

57:02.502 --> 57:04.045
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

57:07.549 --> 57:09.300
I said you don't have to get anything.

57:11.010 --> 57:13.096
How do I look today?
Should I fix anything?

57:14.347 --> 57:15.348
You look stunning.

57:18.017 --> 57:19.102
I'm so nervous.

57:19.602 --> 57:20.895
Stay right by my side, okay?

57:22.063 --> 57:23.648
I've never seen you this nervous.

57:24.065 --> 57:25.733
What if they won't let me marry you?

58:11.112 --> 58:12.655
- Hello.
- Welcome.

58:16.284 --> 58:18.495
- Welcome.
- It's nice to meet you.

58:19.996 --> 58:20.997
It's for you, Mother.

58:21.623 --> 58:24.918
My gosh,
you didn't have to get us anything.

58:25.001 --> 58:26.794
- Ms. Lee!
- Eun-u.

58:27.921 --> 58:28.755
Come here.

58:29.255 --> 58:30.757
- How have you been?
- Good.

58:31.299 --> 58:32.467
I missed you.

58:34.469 --> 58:36.846
What if she makes

58:38.097 --> 58:40.642
some blunt remarks
in front of his parents?

58:41.434 --> 58:43.269
I don't even expect her to impress them.

58:43.394 --> 58:45.104
As long as she doesn't make mistakes.

58:45.188 --> 58:49.067
Anyway, I won't keep you.
I'll call you again later.

58:50.276 --> 58:51.194
Who was that?

58:53.029 --> 58:54.030
Seo-in.

58:54.656 --> 58:55.990
What kind of mistake?

58:56.699 --> 58:58.618
She's getting a divorce, so what else?

59:00.995 --> 59:03.957
It's already been decided,
so just let it go.

59:05.208 --> 59:08.086
And just remember
that she has it the hardest.

59:10.088 --> 59:12.131
What about how we feel as her parents?

59:16.052 --> 59:17.303
When it comes to children,

59:19.764 --> 59:23.101
the more you expect,
the more you're let down.

59:26.479 --> 59:27.480
Let's

59:28.273 --> 59:32.277
neither expect too much from them
nor pressure them in any way.

59:32.777 --> 59:34.445
Let's be that kind of parents.

59:35.321 --> 59:38.783
Okay? That's how I want to be
with our daughters, honey.

59:39.951 --> 59:41.077
Jeez.

59:46.749 --> 59:47.792
Why don't we

59:48.918 --> 59:52.046
go to a nice restaurant for dinner
this evening?

59:53.840 --> 59:54.757
Sounds good?

59:54.882 --> 59:57.468
- What's this one's name?
- The Ankylosaurus.

59:57.552 --> 59:59.846
The Ankylosaurus?
Shall we look for it in the book?

01:00:00.888 --> 01:00:01.806
Oh, there it is.

01:00:01.889 --> 01:00:05.101
- Hey, shouldn't we celebrate with a drink?
- The face is...

01:00:05.852 --> 01:00:07.020
Mom will yell at you again.

01:00:08.062 --> 01:00:10.898
- No, she won't.
- Wow, the Tyrannosaurus...

01:00:11.316 --> 01:00:12.859
You can drink, right?

01:00:14.360 --> 01:00:15.612
Dad.

01:00:16.070 --> 01:00:18.906
I mean, everyone enjoys
having a couple of drinks these days.

01:00:19.407 --> 01:00:20.950
Yes, I like to drink.

01:00:22.243 --> 01:00:23.536
Forget tea.

01:00:24.329 --> 01:00:25.872
Hey, what do you want to drink?

01:00:27.915 --> 01:00:30.126
- Well...
- Ji-ho quit drinking.

01:00:31.669 --> 01:00:33.254
I'm so happy to hear that.

01:00:33.671 --> 01:00:35.632
Who came up with such an amazing idea?

01:00:41.137 --> 01:00:43.348
My dad said he's met you before.

01:00:45.975 --> 01:00:49.979
Right, we met by chance
before he joined the Assembly.

01:00:50.980 --> 01:00:53.858
You must've impressed him that day.
He's talked about you often.

01:00:57.904 --> 01:01:01.491
My dad told me a lot about you as well.
I heard you're very capable.

01:01:02.909 --> 01:01:06.162
I guess he doesn't know that there are
many young professors these days.

01:01:15.213 --> 01:01:17.006
When was your last relationship?

01:01:23.971 --> 01:01:25.431
Let me think.

01:01:26.557 --> 01:01:28.059
I don't really remember.

01:01:30.228 --> 01:01:31.312
Right.

01:01:31.396 --> 01:01:34.482
A past you're not happy with
won't help your present in any way.

01:01:37.527 --> 01:01:40.071
Right, that's a good point.

01:01:42.615 --> 01:01:45.910
So? Are you interested in getting married?

01:01:48.788 --> 01:01:50.206
Obviously, that's why I'm here.

01:01:52.709 --> 01:01:53.751
And...

01:01:55.002 --> 01:01:57.547
I was just thinking that I'm glad
I decided to come here today.

01:02:12.395 --> 01:02:13.354
Oh, thank you.

01:02:16.065 --> 01:02:17.775
Drink slowly.

01:02:19.819 --> 01:02:22.196
He can be quite impulsive,
so you have to be careful.

01:02:22.488 --> 01:02:24.615
Oh, no. I can be impulsive too.

01:02:31.456 --> 01:02:32.498
Is he asleep now?

01:02:36.252 --> 01:02:37.253
Are you all right?

01:02:39.547 --> 01:02:40.923
It looks like you drank a lot.

01:02:41.424 --> 01:02:42.300
No, not at all.

01:02:42.383 --> 01:02:45.303
When else will we have an excuse
to drink like this if not today?

01:02:45.845 --> 01:02:47.513
I'm going to visit you often though.

01:02:50.475 --> 01:02:51.559
Take it easy there.

01:02:51.976 --> 01:02:54.312
I have to be honest. Right?

01:02:54.437 --> 01:02:56.063
Yes, of course. Here.

01:02:58.065 --> 01:02:58.983
My goodness.

01:03:00.651 --> 01:03:02.612
I like Ji-ho more than he likes me.

01:03:02.820 --> 01:03:04.822
At first, he didn't even want to date me.

01:03:14.040 --> 01:03:16.459
I should tell you this
before I get too drunk.

01:03:17.835 --> 01:03:20.463
I know that both of you
are still very worried.

01:03:21.088 --> 01:03:23.841
But I hope you can worry a little less.

01:03:25.301 --> 01:03:28.221
We'll be considerate of each other
and be happy together.

01:03:29.722 --> 01:03:34.852
And I'll do my best
to be a good mom to Eun-u.

01:04:33.995 --> 01:04:35.037
Oh, no.

01:05:14.327 --> 01:05:15.870
Why didn't you take me home?

01:05:16.829 --> 01:05:20.166
Gosh, you're the one
who insisted on sleeping here.

01:05:20.583 --> 01:05:23.085
You went all out.
You drank hard liquor as well as soju.

01:05:23.169 --> 01:05:24.337
You should've stopped me!

01:05:25.796 --> 01:05:28.215
How can I sneak out?
Your mom must be mad at me.

01:05:29.216 --> 01:05:31.052
Yes, she's so mad at you.

01:05:31.427 --> 01:05:33.387
- Crap.
- She said she can't let you marry me.

01:05:33.763 --> 01:05:35.056
Gosh, what do I do?

01:05:35.723 --> 01:05:36.807
What should I do, then?

01:05:37.850 --> 01:05:41.395
It's all right. My dad is very happy
that he now has a new drinking buddy.

01:05:42.271 --> 01:05:44.273
But you said your mom
won't let me marry you.

01:05:46.108 --> 01:05:49.320
- You'll still marry me though.
- Right, I will.

01:05:53.074 --> 01:05:55.660
By the way, where did you sleep?

01:05:57.078 --> 01:05:58.204
How could I have slept,

01:05:58.996 --> 01:06:00.498
knowing that you're in this room?

01:06:00.831 --> 01:06:02.166
You should've sneaked in.

01:06:03.167 --> 01:06:04.210
Gosh, you.

01:06:06.754 --> 01:06:08.047
How am I going to sneak out?

01:06:10.341 --> 01:06:11.467
Before you leave...

01:06:24.188 --> 01:06:26.107
- Here.
- My stomach is upset.

01:06:28.567 --> 01:06:30.653
- Gosh, my stomach...
- Your stomach is upset?

01:06:30.736 --> 01:06:31.779
- Yes.
- It's upset?

01:06:31.862 --> 01:06:33.406
- Yes, for real.
- It doesn't seem so.

01:06:33.489 --> 01:06:36.117
- Here, write your pledge.
- Oh, my stomach...

01:06:36.951 --> 01:06:39.370
Come on. Write your pledge, okay?

01:06:39.662 --> 01:06:40.788
My stomach hurts...

01:06:41.831 --> 01:06:42.873
Gosh, it's killing me.

01:06:55.636 --> 01:06:59.932
I WILL NEVER LIE. ENGAGEMENT WITH
JEONG-IN TO BE BROKEN OFF UPON VIOLATION.

01:07:00.016 --> 01:07:02.560
JUNE 26, 2019, YU JI-HO

01:07:19.452 --> 01:07:21.912
I, LEE JEONG-IN, WILL MARRY YU JI-HO
NO MATTER WHAT

01:07:23.831 --> 01:07:29.170
IF NOT, I'LL STAY SINGLE FOREVER
JULY 6, 2019, LEE JEONG-IN

01:07:54.278 --> 01:07:55.738
Thank you for coming to me.

01:08:12.588 --> 01:08:16.217
Spring brought you to me.

01:08:26.769 --> 01:08:30.022
WOORI PHARMACY

01:08:49.625 --> 01:08:51.377
You said you'd call me
when you were leaving.

01:08:52.211 --> 01:08:54.880
Hello,
do you have any medicine for hangovers?

01:08:58.134 --> 01:08:59.468
Don't you need a rubber band too?

01:09:01.220 --> 01:09:02.638
No, I don't look so bad today.

01:09:05.516 --> 01:09:07.852
- Should I open the medicine for you?
- If you'd like.

01:09:09.436 --> 01:09:11.689
I don't do it for women
who brought their wallets.

01:09:26.036 --> 01:09:27.079
Just a moment, please.

01:10:08.621 --> 01:10:09.622
Ji-ho.

01:12:32.014 --> 01:12:35.768
THE END
